occupation: Senior Digital Analyst at McKinsey & Company
headline: Senior Software Engineer at McKinsey & Company
summary:
I am a Software Engineer with a passion for people and Artificial Intelligence. 

Over my 4 years of college, I served as President of the Student Government for 2 years, a Resident Assistant, as well as an active member of various societies . 

I led one of the top 10 finalist teams in a university-wide $100,000 Artificial Intelligence challenge. 

For senior design project, we implemented trained and developed a Machine Learning Model to offer a cloud based video surveillance service to detect and predict crime in real-time. We received the first place award for the project

experiences.title: Co-Founder
experiences.description:
My responsibilities included managing our engineering team in Erie and Ukraine by working with the team to find solutions to the various problems and challenges that we faced. 

Day to day I’d be involved in everything from Software Architecture, CI/CD pipeline, QA, Presentations to clients, Agile Planning, Development and much more.

The systems we managed did everything from warehousing, international/domestic shipping, accounting and integrations with our vendors and clients.

accomplishment_projects.title: FeelLike
accomplishment_projects.description: We were selected among the top 10 finalists from the 70+ teams that applied. Our Idea was pretty simple, we wanted to get users involved with each other while providing a level of anonymity.

accomplishment_projects.title: Cloud based Intelligent Video Surveillance and Predictive Monitoring Platform
accomplishment_projects.description:
Background: Video Surveillance has become more and more widespread and is being increasingly used in both public and private sectors in a variety of applications - public surveillance, theft detection, natural disasters, fire, vandalism, traffic monitoring etc.

Objective: The objective of this project is to augment Concurrent's Video Platform with cloud based video surveillance capabilities so that Concurrent can offer product(s)/services in this growing Video surveillance market segment.

accomplishment_projects.title: University Food Ordering system, Sonurb
accomplishment_projects.description: Worked in a team of 3 to develop a prototype program for university housing and food services that will allow students to order ‘to go food’ from their phones to increase overall efficiency and decrease waiting times.  We designed the user, kitchen and manager interfaces as well as the database to handle the requests. The final system mainly used MySQL and Java.
